From: Daniel Flanagan <daniel@lyte.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] scim migrations: allow canonical oauth2 client creation

The migration create whitelist for OAuth2ResourceServer entries makes
creating an oauth2 client via SCIM migrations impossible:

- it omits oauth2_rs_origin_landing, which the schema declares MUST
  (AccessDenied when supplied, MissingMustAttribute when omitted)
- it clears the class set to the three oauth2 classes, excluding
  "account" — but the canonical entry shape (what the HTTP API creates,
  server/core/src/https/v1_oauth2.rs) includes EntryClass::Account, whose
  MUST displayname is read back by the commit-time oauth2 config reload
  (idm/oauth2.rs Oauth2ResourceServersWriteTransaction::reload) — a
  whitelist-shaped entry that passes schema then aborts the whole
  transaction with InvalidValueState at commit.

Admit the Account class plus displayname, origin_landing, and the common
policy toggles so migrations can create entries in the same shape the
HTTP API does. Account is not in PROTECTED_MOD_PRES_ENTRY_CLASSES, so
this does not bypass protected-class handling.

--- a/server/lib/src/server/access/migration.rs
+++ b/server/lib/src/server/access/migration.rs
@@ -113,19 +113,25 @@
     if classes.contains(EntryClass::OAuth2ResourceServer.into()) {
         allow_cls.clear();
         allow_cls.extend([
             EntryClass::OAuth2ResourceServer.as_ref(),
             EntryClass::OAuth2ResourceServerBasic.as_ref(),
             EntryClass::OAuth2ResourceServerPublic.as_ref(),
+            EntryClass::Account.as_ref(),
         ]);
         allow_attrs.extend([
             Attribute::Name,
+            Attribute::DisplayName,
             Attribute::Description,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsScopeMap,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsSupScopeMap,
+            Attribute::OAuth2RsOriginLanding,
+            Attribute::OAuth2StrictRedirectUri,
+            Attribute::OAuth2AllowLocalhostRedirect,
+            Attribute::OAuth2AllowInsecureClientDisablePkce,
             Attribute::OAuth2JwtLegacyCryptoEnable,
             Attribute::OAuth2PreferShortUsername,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsClaimMap,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsOrigin,
             Attribute::OAuth2ConsentPromptEnable,
         ])
     }
